
Overview of verb victimize

The verb victimize has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) victimize, victimise -- (make a victim of; "I was victimized by this con-man")
2. (1) victimize, victimise -- (punish unjustly)
3. victimize, swindle, rook, goldbrick, nobble, diddle, bunco, defraud, scam, mulct, gyp, gip, hornswoggle, short-change, con -- (deprive of by deceit; "He swindled me out of my inheritance"; "She defrauded the customers who trusted her"; "the cashier gypped me when he gave me too little change")
